<article id="post-115" class="post-115 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Lecture on legitimacy and crime control</h1>

				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://crim.law.ox.ac.uk/lecture-on-legitimacy-and-crime-control/" title="2:37 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2012-12-12T14:37:59+00:00">12 December 2012</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://crim.law.ox.ac.uk/author/ben-bradford/" title="View all posts by ben.bradford" rel="author">ben.bradford</a></span></span>		</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>On 29<sup>th</sup> November, Ian Loader delivered the 2012 Tsai Lecture at the Nathanson Centre on Transnational Human Rights, Crime and Security. The Nathanson Centre is part of Osgoode Hall Law School at York University in Toronto. Ian spoke on the topic of ‘Legitimacy, Crime Control and Democratic Politics’ . His lecture <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IOgli5LZ4ro ">can be viewed here</a>.</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-meta">
		This entry was posted in <a href="http://crim.law.ox.ac.uk/category/uncategorized/" rel="category tag">Uncategorized</a> by <a href="http://crim.law.ox.ac.uk/author/ben-bradford/">ben.bradford</a>. Bookmark the <a href="http://crim.law.ox.ac.uk/lecture-on-legitimacy-and-crime-control/" title="Permalink to Lecture on legitimacy and crime control" rel="bookmark">permalink</a>.		
